We are given that $PA=PO$. We have
\begin{align*} PA^2 &= (x-10)^2 + (-x+6-(-10))^2 \\ &= (x-10)^2 + (-x+16)^2 \\ &= x^2 - 20x + 100 + x^2 - 32x + 256 \\ &= 2x^2 - 52x + 356 \end{align*}
and
\begin{align*} PO^2 &= (x-0)^2 + (-x+6-0)^2 \\ &= x^2 + (-x+6)^2 \\ &= x^2 + x^2 - 12x + 36 \\ &= 2x^2 - 12x + 36 \end{align*}
